# üß™ Amazon.com - Manual Test Scripts for Automation
## Detailed Test Cases for Selenium Automation

**Prepared by:** Manual QA Team  
**For:** Automation Engineering Team  
**Application:** Amazon.com (E-commerce Platform)  
**Date:** December 22, 2024  
**Environment:** Production (amazon.com)

---

## üìã **Test Script Format**

Each test script includes:
- **Test Case ID** - Unique identifier
- **Test Objective** - What we're validating
- **Pre-conditions** - Setup required before test
- **Test Data** - Specific data to use
- **Detailed Steps** - Step-by-step actions with element locators
- **Expected Results** - What should happen at each step
- **Post-conditions** - Cleanup required
- **Automation Notes** - Tips for automation engineer

---

## üîç **MODULE 1: SEARCH FUNCTIONALITY**
---

### **TC_AMZ_001: Verify Valid Product Search**

**Priority:** HIGH | **Type:** Smoke Test | **Automation:** YES

**Test Objective:**  
Validate that searching with a valid keyword returns relevant product results

**Pre-conditions:**
- Browser is open
- Navigate to https://www.amazon.com
- No items in cart (start fresh)

**Test Data:**
```
Search Keyword: "laptop"
Expected Min Results: 50
```

**Detailed Test Steps:**

| Step | Action | Element Details | Expected Result | Automation Notes |
|------|--------|----------------|----------------|------------------|
| 1 | Navigate to Amazon homepage | URL: https://www.amazon.com | Homepage loads successfully | `driver.get("https://www.amazon.com")` |
| 2 | Locate search box | ID: `twotabsearchtextbox`<br>Type: input text field | Search box is visible and enabled | `WebElement searchBox = driver.findElement(By.id("twotabsearchtextbox"))` |
| 3 | Clear existing text (if any) | Same as Step 2 | Search box is empty | `searchBox.clear()` |
| 4 | Enter search keyword "laptop" | Same as Step 2 | Text "laptop" appears in search box | `searchBox.sendKeys("laptop")` |
| 5 | Locate search button | ID: `nav-search-submit-button`<br>Type: button | Search button is visible | `WebElement searchBtn = driver.findElement(By.id("nav-search-submit-button"))` |
| 6 | Click search button | Same as Step 5 | Search results page loads | `searchBtn.click()` |
| 7 | Wait for results to load | CSS: `[data-component-type="s-search-result"]`<br>Wait: 10 seconds | Results appear on page | `wait.until(visibilityOfElementLocated(By.cssSelector("[data-component-type='s-search-result']")))` |
| 8 | Verify results count text | XPATH: `//span[contains(text(),'results for')]`<br>or<br>CSS: `.sg-col-inner` | Text shows "X results for 'laptop'" | Extract text and validate |
| 9 | Count number of product cards | CSS: `[data-component-type="s-search-result"]` | Count ‚â• 50 products | `List<WebElement> results = driver.findElements(By.cssSelector("[data-component-type='s-search-result']"))` |
| 10 | Verify first product has image | CSS: `.s-image` (within first result) | Image is displayed | Check `isDisplayed()` |
| 11 | Verify first product has title | CSS: `.a-size-medium.a-color-base.a-text-normal` | Title text is present | Check text is not empty |
| 12 | Verify first product has price | CSS: `.a-price-whole` | Price is displayed | Check element exists |

**Expected Final Result:**
- Search results page displays
- Minimum 50 products shown
- Each product has: image, title, price
- Results are relevant to "laptop"

**Post-conditions:**
- Stay on search results page
- Browser remains open for next test

**Automation Notes:**
```java
// Use explicit wait for dynamic elements
WebDriverWait wait = new WebDriverWait(driver, Duration.ofSeconds(10));

// Store results count for validation
int resultsCount = driver.findElements(By.cssSelector("[data-component-type='s-search-result']")).size();
Assert.assertTrue(resultsCount >= 50, "Expected at least 50 results");

// Validate first product
WebElement firstProduct = driver.findElement(By.cssSelector("[data-component-type='s-search-result']"));
Assert.assertTrue(firstProduct.findElement(By.cssSelector(".s-image")).isDisplayed());
```

