### **TC_AMZ_007: Remove Item from Cart**

**Priority:** HIGH | **Type:** Functional Test | **Automation:** YES

**Test Objective:**  
Validate that clicking "Delete" removes item from cart completely

**Pre-conditions:**
- Execute TC_AMZ_006 (3 items in cart)
- Currently on cart page

**Test Data:**
```
Items in Cart: 3 (from previous test)
Action: Remove all items
```

**Detailed Test Steps:**

| Step | Action | Element Details | Expected Result | Automation Notes |
|------|--------|----------------|----------------|------------------|
| 1 | Verify cart has items | Check cart count | Shows "3" | - |
| 2 | Locate "Delete" button | XPATH: `//input[@value='Delete']` or<br>CSS: `input[data-action='delete']` | Delete button visible | `driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[@value='Delete']"))` |
| 3 | Store item count before | ID: `nav-cart-count` | Count = 3 | `int beforeCount = Integer.parseInt(element.getText())` |
| 4 | Click "Delete" button | Same as Step 2 | Button clicked | `element.click()` |
| 5 | Wait for cart update | Wait: 2-3 seconds | Page refreshes | `wait.until(...)` |
| 6 | Verify item removed | Check if product still exists | Product row disappears | `Assert.assertEquals(0, driver.findElements(By.cssSelector(".sc-list-item")).size())` |
| 7 | Verify cart count updated | ID: `nav-cart-count` | Shows "0" | Compare with before count |
| 8 | Verify empty cart message | XPATH: `//*[contains(text(),'Your Amazon Cart is empty')]` or similar | Message displays | Text validation |
| 9 | Verify subtotal removed | Subtotal section | Shows $0.00 or not displayed | Check element |
| 10 | Verify "Proceed to checkout" hidden | Button should not be visible | Button not displayed | `Assert.assertFalse(element.isDisplayed())` |

**Expected Final Result:**
- Item successfully removed
- Cart shows "empty" state
- Cart count = 0
- No checkout button visible
- Empty cart message displayed

**Automation Notes:**
```java
// Click delete
driver.findElement(By.xpath("//input[@value='Delete']")).click();

// Wait for cart to update (handle AJAX or page reload)
wait.until(ExpectedConditions.textToBe(By.id("nav-cart-count"), "0"));

// Verify empty state
boolean emptyMessageDisplayed = driver.findElements(
    By.xpath("//*[contains(text(),'Your Amazon Cart is empty')]")
).size() > 0;
Assert.assertTrue(emptyMessageDisplayed, "Empty cart message not shown");

// Verify no checkout button
boolean checkoutExists = driver.findElements(By.name("proceedToCheckout")).size() > 0;
Assert.assertFalse(checkoutExists, "Checkout button should not be visible");
```

