### **TC_AMZ_008: Proceed to Checkout (Guest User)**

**Priority:** CRITICAL | **Type:** Smoke Test | **Automation:** YES

**Test Objective:**  
Validate that user can proceed to checkout and reach address entry page

**Pre-conditions:**
- Add at least 1 item to cart (execute TC_AMZ_005)
- User is NOT logged in (guest user)

**Test Data:**
```
Email: test_automation_user@example.com
Note: Do NOT complete checkout (stop before payment)
```

**Detailed Test Steps:**

| Step | Action | Element Details | Expected Result | Automation Notes |
|------|--------|----------------|----------------|------------------|
| 1 | Add item to cart | Execute TC_AMZ_005 | 1 item in cart | Reuse previous test |
| 2 | Navigate to cart page | Click cart icon | Cart page loads | - |
| 3 | Locate "Proceed to checkout" | ID: `sc-buy-box-ptc-button` or<br>Name: `proceedToCheckout` | Button visible and enabled | `driver.findElement(By.name("proceedToCheckout"))` |
| 4 | Click "Proceed to checkout" | Same as Step 3 | Button clicked | `element.click()` |
| 5 | Wait for sign-in page load | URL contains `/signin` or `/ap/signin` | Sign-in page displays | `wait.until(urlContains("/signin"))` |
| 6 | Check for email input field | ID: `ap_email` or Name: `email` | Input field visible | - |
| 7 | Enter email address | Same as Step 6 | Email appears in field | `element.sendKeys("test@example.com")` |
| 8 | Click "Continue" button | ID: `continue` | Button clicked | `element.click()` |
| 9 | **STOP HERE** | - | - | **DO NOT PROCEED FURTHER** |
| 10 | Verify URL or page content | Check for password field or address form | Appropriate next step displays | Validate without proceeding |

**Expected Final Result:**
- Checkout process initiates
- Sign-in/email page appears
- Email can be entered
- **Test stops before password/payment entry**

**Post-conditions:**
- Exit checkout flow
- Clear cart if needed for next test

**Automation Notes:**
```java
// Proceed to checkout
driver.findElement(By.name("proceedToCheckout")).click();

// Wait for sign-in page
wait.until(urlContains("/signin"));

// Verify email field exists
boolean emailFieldExists = driver.findElements(By.id("ap_email")).size() > 0;
Assert.assertTrue(emailFieldExists, "Email field not found");

// Enter test email
driver.findElement(By.id("ap_email")).sendKeys("test@example.com");

// Click continue
driver.findElement(By.id("continue")).click();

// IMPORTANT: STOP HERE - Do not proceed to payment
// Verify next step appears but don't complete

// Clean up: Navigate back to homepage
driver.get("https://www.amazon.com");
```

**‚ö†Ô∏è CRITICAL NOTES:**
- **DO NOT complete actual checkout**
- **DO NOT enter real payment information**
- **DO NOT create fake accounts repeatedly**
- This test validates checkout flow initiation only
- For full checkout testing, use Amazon's test environment (if available)

