### **TC_AMZ_009: Empty Search Validation (Negative Test)**

**Priority:** MEDIUM | **Type:** Negative Test | **Automation:** YES

**Test Objective:**  
Validate system behavior when search is submitted without entering any keyword

**Pre-conditions:**
- Navigate to Amazon homepage

**Test Data:**
```
Search Keyword: [empty/blank]
```

**Detailed Test Steps:**

| Step | Action | Element Details | Expected Result | Automation Notes |
|------|--------|----------------|----------------|------------------|
| 1 | Navigate to homepage | URL: amazon.com | Homepage loads | - |
| 2 | Locate search box | ID: `twotabsearchtextbox` | Search box visible | - |
| 3 | Ensure search box is empty | Same | No text in box | `element.clear()` |
| 4 | Click search button directly | ID: `nav-search-submit-button` | Button clicked | `element.click()` |
| 5 | Observe behavior | Wait: 2 seconds | Page may stay on homepage OR show all products | Either is acceptable |
| 6 | Verify no error message | Check for error alerts | No error displayed | System handles gracefully |
| 7 | Verify URL | Current URL | Should not navigate to `/s?k=` with empty param | Check URL pattern |

**Expected Result:**
- System handles empty search gracefully
- No crash or error message
- Either stays on homepage OR shows all products

**Automation Notes:**
```java
driver.findElement(By.id("twotabsearchtextbox")).clear();
driver.findElement(By.id("nav-search-submit-button")).click();
Thread.sleep(2000);

String currentUrl = driver.getCurrentUrl();
// Verify system didn't crash (any response is acceptable)
Assert.assertTrue(currentUrl.contains("amazon.com"), "Page navigated incorrectly");
```

