### **TC_AMZ_010: Cart Persistence After Page Refresh**

**Priority:** MEDIUM | **Type:** Functional Test | **Automation:** YES

**Test Objective:**  
Validate that cart items persist after browser refresh

**Pre-conditions:**
- Add 1-2 items to cart
- Currently on any Amazon page

**Test Data:**
```
Items in Cart: 2
```

**Detailed Test Steps:**

| Step | Action | Element Details | Expected Result | Automation Notes |
|------|--------|----------------|----------------|------------------|
| 1 | Add 2 items to cart | Execute TC_AMZ_005 twice | Cart count = 2 | - |
| 2 | Note cart count | ID: `nav-cart-count` | Shows "2" | `int beforeRefresh = Integer.parseInt(element.getText())` |
| 3 | Refresh the page | Browser refresh | Page reloads | `driver.navigate().refresh()` |
| 4 | Wait for page load | Wait: 3 seconds | Page fully loaded | `wait.until(...)` |
| 5 | Check cart count again | ID: `nav-cart-count` | Still shows "2" | `int afterRefresh = Integer.parseInt(element.getText())` |
| 6 | Navigate to cart page | Click cart icon | Cart page loads | - |
| 7 | Verify items still present | Product listings | Both products visible | Count items |
| 8 | Verify quantities | Quantity selectors | Quantities unchanged | - |

**Expected Result:**
- Cart persists after refresh
- No items lost
- Quantities remain same

**Automation Notes:**
```java
int beforeRefresh = Integer.parseInt(driver.findElement(By.id("nav-cart-count")).getText());

driver.navigate().refresh();
wait.until(visibilityOfElementLocated(By.id("nav-cart-count")));

int afterRefresh = Integer.parseInt(driver.findElement(By.id("nav-cart-count")).getText());
Assert.assertEquals(beforeRefresh, afterRefresh, "Cart items lost after refresh");
```

